# COMP7640 Database Systems & Administration - Group Project Assignment
## COMP 7640: Group Course Project
Group Enrollment Due: 11:59 PM, Feb 12 (Thu), 2026
Submission Due: 11:59 PM, April 15 (Wed), 2026

## Objective
In this project, each group is tasked with the creation and execution of an e-commerce platform for multiple vendors and customers with a focus on personalized user experiences.

## Basic Requirements
- Vendors: Each vendor on the platform will maintain a unique profile that includes a vendor ID, business name, average rating from customers, geographical presence, and an inventory of products.
- Products: Each product is identified by a unique product ID, has a name, a listed price, a stock quantity, and up to three tags that encapsulate the product's nature, which are set by the vendor that sells it. Products can be associated with multiple orders.
- Customers: A comprehensive database must be maintained for customers, each of whom has a unique customer ID, contact number, shipping address, and order history. Customers can place multiple orders.
- Orders: Each order has a unique order ID, customer ID, order date, a list of products and their quantities, total price, and status. A single order can include transactions that span multiple vendors.
- Transactions: Every purchase transaction is associated with an order from a customer, the payment from one customer to a vendor, and involves at least one product from the vendor’s catalog.

## Required Functionalities
### Vendor Administration:
The platform should enable functionality to
1. Display a listing of all vendors
2. Onboard new vendors onto the marketplace.

### Product Catalog Management:
Users are allowed to
1. Browse all products offered by each vendor
2. Introduce new products to a vendor's catalog.

### Product Discovery:
The system must facilitate a search feature that allows users to discover products using tags. The search should return products where the tag matches any part of the product's name or its associated tags.

### Product Purchase:
The system should support product purchasing and record in the database which customer purchases which product.

### Order Modification:
Users must have the option to modify their orders, including the removal of specific products or the cancellation of the entire order before it enters the shipping process.

## System Implementation
Write a Java or Python program (command line interface or GUI, both are fine) to implement the e-commerce platform and required functions. For software versions:
Java 11 (or above) and Python 3.5 (or above) are strongly recommended, while other versions might fail on departmental computers and affect the grading.
- Use JDBC and PyMySQL to access MySQL from the Java and Python programs, respectively. MySQL is open source and can be freely downloaded here.

## Project Schedule
The project should be carried out in groups of 5-6 members, which includes two phases.

### Phase 1: Group forming
Each group should have a group leader and complete the group enrollment on HKBU Moodle by 11:59 PM, February 12th, 2026. Kindly note that each group will be graded using the same standard regardless of the number of members. If you fail to enroll in any group before the due date, you will be assigned to a group randomly. Each member of the same group will receive the same marks, so you need to form your group carefully and learn how to collaborate with your group members.

### Phase 2: Database design & System implementation
1. Each group must design an ER diagram and convert the diagram to relational tables.
2. Each group must implement the required functionalities.
3. Each group needs to submit a soft copy of the final report and a soft copy of their code of implementation.
4. Each group needs to write a README file to describe how to run your code.
5. Each group needs to record a video, which must be less than or equal to 6 minutes, for selling your e-commerce platform to the course instructors (customers), which includes the design of an ER diagram, the design of relational tables, and the demonstration of functionalities.

